Work crews seal the worst structural cracks, strip out bank-era security hardpoints, and partition the pyramid's vast interior into dormitory stacks.  Third-wave refugees fill the upper tiers; Otherworld arrivals get the dormitories terraced around the pyramid's small artificial lake — the swim-through gate that still links Aurora to the Otherworld.  Children still shout in the echoing halls — but now they do it under city leases instead of squatter truces.

[? if jovian_refugee_prepare = 1: Relief organizers credit the earlier refugee-prep push for having survey teams ready. ?]

@defer
title: Stall — keep negotiating with the squatters
on-arrival: aurora_pyramid_housing_deferred = 1

The council kicks the decision down the road.  Squatters and ICA freelancers keep the pyramid as a patchwork commune while refugees pile up in Aurora's parks.  TODO: follow-up event or timed re-trigger when `aurora_pyramid_housing_deferred = 1`.

